All four teenagers have previously acknowledged they were throwing the homemade bombs 'to scare some of their other friends,' Unified Fire Authority investigator Steve Bowen said in a court affidavit.

'We don't really understand a clear reason for their behavior,' prosecutor Blake Nakamura said earlier this month. 'The reason we charged them is obviously, what they possessed was indeed explosives, and we're alleging they were throwing them near homes and at people, and therefore, had the potential to cause a great deal of harm.'

